modules.description: Converts calendar durations to ICS format and maps calendar properties to their ICS key strings. Works with `Ptime.Span.t` for time spans and `Icalendar.cal_prop` for calendar properties. Useful for serializing event durations and property keys into ICS files.

This module handles date and time manipulations, recurrence rule definitions, and structured representation of calendar components like events and timezones. It operates on timestamp and recurrence types (e.g., `recur`, `freq`) with timezone-awareness, along with property parameters for calendar data. Specific use cases include generating ICS files, managing recurring events with custom rules, and handling participant status or free/busy information in calendar applications.
